item.title: Will Santa hats reach 20m+ again?
item.dc:creator: @billygotshot billygotshot
item.description:
@billygotshot wrote:

[quote=“davidude36, post:8, topic:168719”][quote author=billygotshot link=topic=228341.msg1960919#msg1960919 date=1198958469]

Some people wouldn’t believe that in october 06 santa hats were 26m-27m, blue masks were almost 40m and red masks were 50m.

And then there is those dumbass people who say “INVEST IN RARES, THEY ALWAYS GO UP”
According to the grand exchange santa hats are 16-17m, that is 10m lower then what they were about 14 months ago.

because jagex controls the economy now. like they should have from the begining… that is the whole point of the grand exchange. they can make the price any amount they want it to be. Jagex HATES rares they didnt want them to be worth alot because it is bad for the economy.
[/quote]
Well i don’t believe it is completely jagex that is lowering the price of rares, because santas steadily dropped to 20m (from 26m) before the grand exchange was even released. But i suppose they are controling it slightly now that the grand exchange is out the santas went from 20m to 16-17m.

Who knows… pure essence before exchange was 60-70ea, now its 120ea…
nats were 300-330ea, now they are 250ea. (basically ruined runecrafting)[/quote]

the whole point of runecrafting was not to make a profit
it was to let players have the ability to make their own runes for a very small amount of money.
